Don't run Prettier against Markdown files

Prettier removes leading spaces from Markdown files, which prevents us
from using the "note" syntax like this:

!!! note
    Here is a note content.
    Here is some other note content.

This commit exempts Markdown files from Prettier in both the frontend
linting script and in VSCode.

Fix notes in CONTRIBUTING.md

Using syntax documented here:

https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/16925#discussioncomment-6682796

Properly indent text in Markdown notes.

pull_request.title: Remove large pull quote
pull_request.body: I noticed the large pull quote is only used on https://www.consumerfinance.gov/data-research/consumer-complaints/ This pattern is very old and goes back to 2014 (added in https://github.com/cfpb/cf-typography/pull/17) We have the "is large" option in Wagtail to support the one use case in the CCDB landing page. Consulting with @natalia-fitzgerald, it was decided it would be fine for this page to have the regular pull quote, which I have updated on the live site. ## Removals - Large pull quote. ## How to test this PR 1. Run `python cfgov/manage.py migrate` and edit a page in Wagtail that has a quote, such as the CCDB landing page, and see there is no longer an "is large" option for the pull quote. ## Screenshots Before: After:

pull_request.title: Use the include format module instead of the format-usd package.
pull_request.body:
In https://github.com/cfpb/consumerfinance.gov/pull/7400 we added format-usd and unformat-usd to `modules`. There was a note in that PR that perhaps we should have a general utils repo/package in the future.. and that time is now!

This PR, though is just moving old references/uses of format-usd/unformat-usd to the new module so that, when we do the refactor, it will be the same type of changes everywhere.
